<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1914-08-18T13:15:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1914-08-17T19:00:00-05:00" n="464" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d464">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 763.72112/87</note>
                            <head>
                                <hi rend="italic">The Consul General at London</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_SRP1" type="from"><hi rend="italic">Skinner</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the</hi>
                                <gloss type="to">
                                    <hi rend="italic">Secretary of State</hi>
                                </gloss>
                            </head>
                            <dateline>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">American Consulate General</hi>, <lb/>
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="italic">London</hi></placeName>, <date ana="#date_undated-inferred-from-document-content" calendar="gregorian" notAfter="1914-08-18T13:15:00-05:00" notBefore="1914-08-18T00:00:00+00:00"><hi rend="italic">undated</hi></date>. <lb/> [<hi rend="italic">Received
                                        <date calendar="gregorian" when="1914-08-18T13:15:00+00:00">
                                        <hi rend="italic">August 18, 1914, 1:15 p.m.</hi>
                                    </date></hi>] </dateline>
                            <p rend="center">[Telegram]</p>
                            <p>Marshal of prize court informs me neutrals can obtain possession of
                                their property not contraband by applying procurator general,
                                Treasury Chambers, Whitehall, who will require proof ownership and
                                particulars as to freight whether paid or unpaid.</p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed>
                                    <persName corresp="#p_SRP1">
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Skinner</hi>
                                    </persName>
                                </signed>
                            </closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>